pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt, long pants, chemical resistant gloves, shoes plus socks, and protective eyewear. Applicators using a high pressure handwand in an enclosed area must wear a NIOSH-approved respirator with a dust/mist filter (MSHA/NIOSH-approval number prefix TC-21C or N, R, P or HE filter). Applicators using hand held foggers in an enclosed area must wear a half-face, full-face or hood-style NIOSH-approved respirator with a dust/mist filtering cartridge (MSHA/NIOSH-approval number prefix TX-21C), a pesticide approved canister (MSHA/NIOSH-approval number prefix TX-14G), or any N, R, P or HE filter.

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed. Prolonged or frequently repeated skin contact may cause allergic reactions in some individuals. Avoid contact with skin or clothing. Wash hands thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Immediately call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or a doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Immediately rinse skin with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
